      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TAKE THE STEPS (1) goes very well at the course with two wins and a placing from four starts. Hit the frame latest (30.28) when third at this track in a Grade 4/5. Looks the one to beat with even luck. CROCODILE ROLL (3) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fourth (30.50) at Angle Park. Solid record at the distance winning five races. Should be about the money. REGAL BARRY (5) is an honest type who is new here. Had a squeeze draw but was too good last time scoring by 1.5 lengths at Angle Park over 530m (30.65). In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. CANYA VIVI (7) jumps at a shorter journey and still warrants respect.",
